1.title: Quantum Leaps
1.plot: We're glimpsing into the internet's biggest breakthroughs, genius inventions and awesome builds that are undeniable quantum leaps. We'll see robot exoskeletons, swords made with thermite and high speed scooters.

2.plot: We're investigating if nature truly knows best. We'll see world's first driving dog, a bright blue tarantula, and the world's smallest horse. This is nature totally uncaged and off the hook!

4.title: This Changes Everything
4.plot: We're breaking new ground with the internet's most astonishing trend setters, ensuring life will never be the same. We'll see a blindfolded man catch an arrow, grizzly bears test products and two people jump into a plane.

5.title: Make it Real
5.plot: We're witnessing the biggest displays of power on the web. We'll learn how to harness the power of water to cut hair, use paper to stop explosions and build the perfect sandcastle to lift a car. Power is the order of the day so brace for impact!

4.title: Power Up

5.title: Game Changers
5.plot: Prepare to follow in the wake of the some of the internet's most ingenious trend setters. We've got never-before-done barrel rolls, dizzying experiments in space, and a bungee jump like no other. We're going to the cutting edge -- and beyond.

6.title: Neighborhood Watch
6.plot: We celebrate the scientific world in our own backyards with some of the wildest homemade Internet videos. Meet the suburban scientists who bathe in Silly Putty and the daredevils who build flying bikes, and find out the truth behind backyard UFOs.

7.title: Beta Testers
7.plot: Problem-solve with some of the best inventors on the web. We watch as these ambitious creators test a kit to fend off sharks, skydive without parachutes, and build DIY scuba gear.

8.title: Fearless or Foolish
8.plot: We're turning the spotlight on both fearless and foolish internet legends. We'll see heart stopping trick shots, extreme mountain unicyclers, and a relaxing hot bath of chilli sauce. These epic skills and fails prove science is one tough Task Master.

9.title: Amped Up
9.plot: We're showcasing the most inventive people on the web. People who've taken a simple idea and turned it up to 11! We'll learn how to get a tattoo from a machine, build an engine from paper, and ride on a giant homemade swing.

10.title: Truth or Troll
10.plot: We'll separate science fact from science fiction. Can a saw made of paper cut wood? Can you take a selfie with a tornado? Do giant gators roam Florida's golf courses? Our experts are on a mission to find the truth and expose the web's greatest trolls.

11.title: Natural Selection
11.plot: We're on an internet expedition in search of Mother Nature's biggest OMG moments. We've got cuddly bears, criminal ferrets and an entire island made from trash. We're on the quest for the weirdest, wildest and wackiest nature lovers on the internet.

12.title: Epic Elements
12.plot: We're boiling science down to its component parts. These pioneers have wrestled with the forces of the universe and faced the elements in order to capture something extraordinary.

13.title: Crowd Pleasers
13.plot: We're counting down the top twenty crowd-pleasers: skilled souls who use their science to thrill. We'll see close encounters in the wild, the world's fastest skateboarder, and a trapeze at 300 feet. Strap yourself in for one extreme ride.

14.title: Moguls of Mayhem
14.plot: We're counting down clips celebrating the fearless innovators who have a genius for anarchy and destruction. From real-life hungry hippos to a firearm symphony shootout, these kings of carnage will showcase science in its most explosive form.

15.title: Pure Power
15.plot: Plug in and witness these mighty individuals as they harness the speed, strength, and skills required to blow the lid off the internet. We'll see outrageous bungee jumps and powerful drones that can fly and swim.

16.title: Bucket List
16.plot: We're creating the ultimate bucket list. We'll learn how to cook bread with a volcano, build underwater hotel rooms, and go eyeball-to-eyeball with Great Whites.

17.title: Mind Benders
17.plot: We're about to blow minds with some of the most mind-bending clips on the web. Our experts taste-test a 100-year-old cracker, witness a real-life transformer car, and listen to guitars played underwater.

1.title: Life Hackers
1.plot: We're turning the spotlight on backyard inventors that are creating the ultimate life hacks. We'll see these geniuses turn a bike into a car, soda into a fire extinguisher, and a jet ski into a Jetovator.

2.title: Tons of Anarchy
2.plot: We're counting down all things carnage! We will see everything from the world's biggest firework to a watermelon-destroying vacuum cannon to a giant fire tornado. One thing is for certain; these individuals have a genius for anarchy and chaos.

3.title: Bragging Rights
3.plot: We're counting down highly skilled show-offs, people who claim their epic skills give them serious bragging rights. These super-skilled individuals blow our minds with tandem unicycles, high altitude dinner parties, and archery with a twist.

4.title: Very Innovative People
4.plot: Our experts have an all-access pass to the most innovative people on the web. Celebrate the people that turn creative ideas into reality, from cardboard boats to jet ski powered water bikes. If there is a new way of doing it, these VIPs will be first.

5.title: Seriously
5.plot: We're bending minds with the freakiest clips on the web. We'll watch a man eat a red hot coal, a robot solve a Rubik's Cube in a second, and a freaky creature with a glowing beak.

6.title: Ground Breakers
6.plot: We're breaking new ground with the internet's most astonishing trend setters. We'll see everything from the world's first mountain bike on skis to a real-life Iron Man suit. These front runners leave all things ordinary in the rear-view mirror.

7.title: No Brainers
7.plot: We're shining the spotlight on internet legends who turn fails into wins. We're serving up excruciating face-masks, helicopter stunts with Bob Burnquist, and astonishing snowmobile stunts.

8.title: Body Rockers
8.plot: We're counting down just how far we can push the human body to it limits. Our experts test homemade gas masks and create music from blood. These are the most extreme body experiments on the web.

9.title: Rebooters
9.plot: We're showcasing the creators who reimagine classic ideas, making them bigger and better than ever. We'll see massive mouse traps, an automatic dartboard, and a 20 foot abominable snowman. You may have seen it before, but you've never seen it like this.

10.title: Masters of Disasters
10.plot: We're counting down the most dangerous clips on the web. Celebrate the fearless people who have mastered disaster by turning it into a scientific endeavor. We'll see explosive artwork, underwater sword swallowing, and a jumbo jet pulled by just one man!

1.title: Strangest Things
1.plot: We're questioning reality with the most mind-melting videos our experts can find. We'll discover see-through animals, algae-powered motorcycles, and a human sized chicken. It's freaky, fantastic and will leave your head spinning.

2.title: Mod Fathers
2.plot: We're turning the spotlight on independent inventors who create astonishing inventions in their backyards. We'll see a precision drone-catcher transform into a vacuum-powered railway and a homemade tank become a hot air balloon.

3.title: Owned It
3.plot: We're counting down the top twenty internet legends. The smartest, brightest, and bravest people who use their science know-how to thrill. We'll see how to light matches with bullets, walk the world's longest highline, and kayak in the snow!

4.title: Supernatural
4.plot: We're hunting down Mother Nature's most amazing moments. We'll witness a man eaten alive by leaches, a rainbow at night, and a man who pulls a car with his eye sockets! These are the weirdest, wildest, and wackiest natural born thrillers.

5.title: How Not To
5.plot: We're counting down the most epic fails with the internet's ultimate mistake makers. These clips are an instruction manual in failure. We'll see a crash at 300 mph, a person freak-out in virtual reality, and a jetpack go catastrophically wrong.

6.title: MVPs
6.plot: We're assembling the internet's Most Valuable Players, the heroes who use science to win the day. We'll see the world's longest manual riding a skateboard, people pulling cars with their teeth, and a person skiing behind a super car.

7.title: Power Trippin'
7.plot: We're searching for people who live to wield their power. These super charged power trippers drop giant knives from cranes, take aim at explosive-packed refrigerators, and pull off the world's first skydive from a drone!

8.title: Masters of Mayhem
8.plot: We're showcasing the web's most destructive minds, people using science to master mayhem! We'll revel in the chaos with epic railguns, incredible punching robots, and amazing bowling ball launchers.

9.title: Ultimate Upgraders
9.plot: We're focusing on bona fide geniuses who are the ultimate upgraders. These garage innovators are taking things to the next level! We'll watch them use fire to charge cell phones, turn garbage into boats, and create the world's fastest electric dragster.

10.title: Mind Blown
10.plot: We're counting down the craziest videos that leave our minds blown. We'll see a double sunset, tattoos that play sound, and a rope climbing moped. These are the internet's most unbelievable videos that only science can explain.
